        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 2:56PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cossatot River State Park, or 11 miles south of Mena, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Board Camp...                     Big Fork...
Shady...                          Hartley...
Nunley...                         Ink...
Opal...                           Acorn...
Mena...                           Y City...
Pine Ridge...                     Cossatot River State Park...
Caney Creek Wilderness...         Cherry Hill in Polk County...
Boles...                          Dallas...
Mena Intermountain Airport...     Mccauley...
Oden...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
western Arkansas.</instruction>
